<subSubSection id="C337088DF77CB13DB182FE2436EF407B" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F77CB13DB182FE2433D04054" blockId="9.[151,1437,403,1293]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">
<materialsCitation id="3B45515BF77CB13DB182FE2433DC4054" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3766756304" collectingDate="1842-02-15" collectingDateMax="1844-03-27" collectingDateMin="1842-02-15" collectionCode="TYPE" county="Apies River" location="Saulspoort" municipality="Tswaing" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" specimenCount="2" stateProvince="Berlin" typeStatus="lectotype">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F77CB13DB182FE2432C242B0" box="[199,251,475,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: Sundevall in his original description referred to characters of both male and female, and according to his acquisition catalogue he had at least 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF77CB13DB3A3FE0031BC415B" box="[742,901,511,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
available at the time. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77CB13DB5C3FE0037A5415B" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[1158,1436,511,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 84)</bibRefCitation>
referred to NRM 569872 [7258] as a “type”; we treat this as a 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F77CB13DB211FDDC3182417F" box="[852,955,547,573]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of this adult male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F77CB13DB4C5FDDD33044123" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" value="1842-02-15">
<collectingDate id="EFD7842EF77CB13DB4C5FDDD33044123" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" value="1842-02-15">15 February 1842</collectingDate>
</date>
at 
<collectingCounty id="62F3238AF77CB13DB024FDB833D54123" box="[353,492,583,609]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">Apies River</collectingCounty>
. The 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF77CB13DB369FDB8313B4123" box="[556,770,583,609]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">five paralectotypes</specimenCount>
