<subSubSection id="C337088DF77CB13DB182FCBC36B4464F" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F77CB13DB182FCBC36B4464F" blockId="9.[151,1437,403,1293]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">
COMMENTS: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77CB13DB00FFCBC3058401F" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[330,609,835,861]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 84</bibRefCitation>
, 115) explained why “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F77CB13DB22DFCBC3735401F" authority="Sundevall, 1850: 108" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityPageNumber="108" authorityYear="1850" box="[872,1292,835,861]" class="Aves" family="Bucerotidae" genus="Buceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bucerotiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="erythrorhynchus" variety="caffer">Buceros erythrorhynchus var. caffer</taxonomicName>
” 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77CB13DB45AFCBC333740C3" author="Sundevall, C. J." pageId="9" pageNumber="530" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall, 1850: 108</bibRefCitation>
was not intended as a new name. Wahlberg collected at Hartebeespoort from 
<date id="FF937DC6F77CB13DB5D5FC99375040C3" box="[1168,1385,870,897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" value="1841-11-15">15 November 1841</date>
to 
<date id="FF937DC6F77CB13DB4CBFC99330940E7" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" value="1842-01-05">5 January 1842</date>
, travelling on this day to Apies River, where he collected until 2 March. He broke camp on 2 March, and on 3 March was “….at the station on the lower Apies River. Walked to the confluence of the Soane and the Moritemi” suggesting that his camp on the Apies River was close to the confluence. The river names are confusing—according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77CB13DB029FC08303F4753" author="Skead, C. J." box="[364,518,1015,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" pagination="1 - 259" refId="ref29709" refString="Skead, C. J. (1973) Zoo Historical Gazetteer. Annals of the Cape Provincial Museums, 10, 1 - 259." type="journal article" year="1973">Skead (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, the “Soane” and the “Moritemi (= Moretele)” rivers are different names for the Apies River, but 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77CB13DB016FBE4300A4777" author="Rookmaaker, L. C." box="[339,563,1051,1077]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" pagination="55 - 198" refId="ref29540" refString="Rookmaaker, L. C. (2007) A chronological survey of bibliographical and iconographical sources on rhinoceroses in southern Africa from 1795 to 1875: reconstructing views on classification and changes in distribution. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Africa, 62 (2), 55 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00359190709519203" type="journal article" year="2007">Rookmaaker (2007)</bibRefCitation>
identified the Moretele and the “Soane” rivers as distinct from the Apies River (
<figureCitation id="13164783F77CB13DB1DAFBC0331D471B" box="[159,292,1087,1113]" captionStart="Appendix 1" captionStartId="37.[151,273,532,558]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Appendix 1: Gazetteer of localities" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">Appendix 1</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77CB13DB078FBC0306C471B" author="Craig, A. &amp; Hummel, C." box="[317,597,1087,1113]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" refId="ref28290" refString="Craig, A. &amp; Hummel, C. (1994) Johan August Wahlberg. Travel Journals (and Some Letters) South Africa and Namibia / Botswana, 1838 - 1856. Translated from Swedish by Michael Roberts. Series 2. No. 23. Van Riebeeck Society, Cape Town, 249 pp." type="book" year="1994">Craig &amp; Hummel (1994)</bibRefCitation>
noted, probably correctly, that this was the junction between the Moretele (= Apies River) and Tolwane rivers, but it is more likely that Wahlberg confused the river names, and that he was at the confluence between the Apies and Pienaar’s rivers on 
<date id="FF937DC6F77CB13DB204FB7831E447E3" box="[833,989,1159,1185]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" value="1841-03-03">3 March 1841</date>
—the confluence between the Moretele and the Tolwane is too far to the west of where Wahlberg was camped. Wahlberg did not specify any localities along the Apies River, but 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77CB13DB03AFB30305847AB" author="Rookmaaker, L. C." box="[383,609,1231,1257]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" pagination="55 - 198" refId="ref29540" refString="Rookmaaker, L. C. (2007) A chronological survey of bibliographical and iconographical sources on rhinoceroses in southern Africa from 1795 to 1875: reconstructing views on classification and changes in distribution. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Africa, 62 (2), 55 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00359190709519203" type="journal article" year="2007">Rookmaaker (2007)</bibRefCitation>
suggested he was at the Apies River at 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F77CB13DB567FB31368647AB" box="[1058,1215,1230,1257]" degrees="25" direction="south" minutes="28" orientation="latitude" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" precision="925" value="-25.466667">25° 28’ South</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F77CB13DB58EFB30376C47AB" box="[1227,1365,1230,1257]" degrees="28" direction="east" minutes="15" orientation="longitude" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" precision="925" value="28.25">28° 15’ East</geoCoordinate>
on 13 February. This place can be accepted as the 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F77CB13DB3C6FB0C308A464F" box="[643,691,1267,1293]" pageId="9" pageNumber="530">type</typeStatus>
locality for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F77CB13DB279FB0C36B4464F" authority="Sundevall." authorityName="Sundevall." box="[828,1165,1267,1293]" class="Aves" family="Bucerotidae" genus="Buceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bucerotiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="530" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufirostris">Buceros rufirostris Sundevall.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
